WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.066 --> 00:00:00.633
Scott, I want to

00:00:00.633 --> 00:00:01.901
start with you, because last hour

00:00:01.901 --> 00:00:02.402
you were saying

00:00:02.402 --> 00:00:03.136
basically that you think

00:00:03.136 --> 00:00:04.070
that the Biden administration

00:00:04.070 --> 00:00:06.106
is allowing this whole thing up

00:00:06.106 --> 00:00:07.440
or just not addressing

00:00:07.440 --> 00:00:08.675
what's happening at the border

00:00:08.675 --> 00:00:10.210
in any kind of effective way.

00:00:10.210 --> 00:00:12.912
What do you want President Biden to do?

00:00:12.946 --> 00:00:13.980
I mean, again,

00:00:13.980 --> 00:00:15.115
the situation at the border is

00:00:15.115 --> 00:00:17.684
so appears to be so overrun,

00:00:17.817 --> 00:00:18.718
so complicated.

00:00:18.718 --> 00:00:20.787
What today can President Biden do?

00:00:22.022 --> 00:00:23.790
Well, he said in his statement in

00:00:23.790 --> 00:00:24.724
the White House is saying

00:00:24.724 --> 00:00:26.292
that they think Republicans should work

00:00:26.292 --> 00:00:26.993
with Democrats.

00:00:26.993 --> 00:00:27.660
And I agree.

00:00:27.660 --> 00:00:29.629
And the Republicans who just took over

00:00:29.629 --> 00:00:30.130
the U.S.

00:00:30.130 --> 00:00:31.698
House unveiled a framework

00:00:31.698 --> 00:00:33.733
for immigration reform in December.

00:00:33.733 --> 00:00:34.367
It includes

00:00:34.367 --> 00:00:35.869
finishing the barrier system

00:00:35.869 --> 00:00:36.903
that started under Trump

00:00:36.903 --> 00:00:37.470
that Biden

00:00:37.470 --> 00:00:38.972
paused recruiting

00:00:38.972 --> 00:00:40.206
and retaining our great Border

00:00:40.206 --> 00:00:41.574
Patrol agents.

00:00:41.574 --> 00:00:43.143
If you can't detain someone

00:00:43.143 --> 00:00:44.544
for the duration of their illegal

00:00:44.544 --> 00:00:46.579
stay here, we should turn them away.

00:00:46.579 --> 00:00:49.149
Asylum reform, targeting the cartels.

00:00:49.149 --> 00:00:50.817
There's an entire framework

00:00:50.817 --> 00:00:52.018
that Republicans laid out

00:00:52.018 --> 00:00:54.120
just a couple of weeks ago

00:00:54.120 --> 00:00:55.655
that they plan to pursue now.

00:00:55.655 --> 00:00:56.756
Will the Senate Democrats

00:00:56.756 --> 00:00:57.457
pick up on that?

00:00:57.457 --> 00:00:58.425
Will the Biden White House

00:00:58.425 --> 00:00:59.159
pick up on that?

00:00:59.159 --> 00:01:01.161
I want to see Joe Biden

00:01:01.161 --> 00:01:02.362
put his money where his mouth is.

00:01:02.362 --> 00:01:04.564
He says he wants bipartisan cooperation.

00:01:04.564 --> 00:01:05.732
The Republicans have a plan.

00:01:05.732 --> 00:01:06.733
They laid it out.

00:01:06.733 --> 00:01:08.101
Maybe that's a starting point.

00:01:08.101 --> 00:01:09.235
Paul, what's

00:01:09.235 --> 00:01:11.004
what are the chances that the Democrats

00:01:11.004 --> 00:01:11.971
would go along with how

00:01:11.971 --> 00:01:12.872
Scott just phrased it?

00:01:14.274 --> 00:01:16.676
Well, Democrats want a solution.

00:01:17.010 --> 00:01:17.977
They want at least to address

00:01:17.977 --> 00:01:20.080
the problem. Republicans want chaos.

00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:21.581
They want chaos at the border

00:01:21.581 --> 00:01:22.382
because they believe

00:01:22.382 --> 00:01:23.850
it helps them politically.

00:01:23.850 --> 00:01:24.250
Ever since

00:01:24.250 --> 00:01:24.784
Donald Trump

00:01:24.784 --> 00:01:26.252
slithered down that escalator,

00:01:26.252 --> 00:01:28.121
they have been demagoguing immigration.

00:01:28.121 --> 00:01:29.789
There is a crisis at the border, though.

00:01:29.789 --> 00:01:30.690
There is.

00:01:30.690 --> 00:01:31.491
And I actually

00:01:31.491 --> 00:01:32.392
think the executive branch,

00:01:32.392 --> 00:01:34.060
President Biden in this case, doing

00:01:34.060 --> 00:01:35.562
everything he can, is plussed up

00:01:35.562 --> 00:01:36.229
the Border Patrol.

00:01:36.229 --> 00:01:37.831
He said he's adding even more agents now.

00:01:37.831 --> 00:01:38.765
They've stopped record amounts

00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:40.834
of fentanyl and record numbers of people.

00:01:40.834 --> 00:01:42.168
The courts are doing all they can.

00:01:42.168 --> 00:01:43.636
In fact, they're doing more

00:01:43.636 --> 00:01:44.571
than they're constitutionally

00:01:44.571 --> 00:01:45.205
allowed to do.

00:01:45.205 --> 00:01:45.772
Even Justice

00:01:45.772 --> 00:01:47.040
Gorsuch pointed that out today.

00:01:47.040 --> 00:01:48.975
They've gone beyond their role.

00:01:48.975 --> 00:01:50.610
Congress has to fix this.

00:01:50.610 --> 00:01:51.878
And the reason Congress hasn't fixed

00:01:51.878 --> 00:01:54.614
it is the Republicans don't want to get.

00:01:54.647 --> 00:01:54.747
I know.

00:01:55.148 --> 00:01:56.216
I don't want I don't mean to interrupt.

00:01:56.216 --> 00:01:57.917
I just want to address what Scott said.

00:01:57.917 --> 00:01:58.585
Scott,

00:01:58.585 --> 00:01:59.886
I know the Democrats always say

00:01:59.886 --> 00:02:00.854
that, that Republicans

00:02:00.854 --> 00:02:01.988
want this as a talking point.

00:02:01.988 --> 00:02:03.423
And Republicans always say that Democrats

00:02:03.423 --> 00:02:04.424
and I'll show up at the table.

00:02:04.424 --> 00:02:05.592
But what about what Scott just said, that

00:02:05.592 --> 00:02:07.160
they've laid out this plan

00:02:07.160 --> 00:02:08.194
but I don't think Will,

00:02:08.194 --> 00:02:09.095
where Democrats go

00:02:09.095 --> 00:02:09.662
along with

00:02:09.662 --> 00:02:11.831
with continuing that border wall,

00:02:12.031 --> 00:02:13.766
would they go along with everything

00:02:13.766 --> 00:02:14.501
that Scott just said?

00:02:16.102 --> 00:02:17.070
They have

00:02:17.070 --> 00:02:18.505
Democrats been working on this for years

00:02:18.505 --> 00:02:19.172
and it has been

00:02:19.172 --> 00:02:20.607
at every critical juncture,

00:02:20.607 --> 00:02:22.375
the Republicans that have tanked it.

00:02:22.375 --> 00:02:22.842
Now, look, there's

00:02:22.842 --> 00:02:23.610
some hope

00:02:23.610 --> 00:02:25.011
it's not coming from the press release

00:02:25.011 --> 00:02:27.413
that Kevin McCarthy's aides put out.

00:02:27.413 --> 00:02:28.982
It comes actually from the Senate side.

00:02:28.982 --> 00:02:29.916
Kirsten Cinema,

00:02:29.916 --> 00:02:31.050
who was a Democrat

00:02:31.050 --> 00:02:32.852
until about 15 minutes ago,

00:02:32.852 --> 00:02:33.720
working with Thom Tillis

00:02:33.720 --> 00:02:35.688
in North Carolina, Republican

00:02:35.688 --> 00:02:37.590
and it's not comprehensive at all,

00:02:37.590 --> 00:02:38.591
but it's a good start.

00:02:38.591 --> 00:02:39.692
Here's what they would do

00:02:39.692 --> 00:02:40.560
increase border

00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:41.394
patrol security,

00:02:41.394 --> 00:02:42.695
increase security at the border,

00:02:42.695 --> 00:02:44.797
reform asylum,

00:02:44.797 --> 00:02:46.766
which is really where a lot of the reason

00:02:46.766 --> 00:02:48.001
a lot of these folks are entering,

00:02:48.001 --> 00:02:50.236
and then clear a path to citizenship

00:02:50.403 --> 00:02:51.437
for these Dreamers.

00:02:51.437 --> 00:02:52.472
It's not everything,

00:02:52.472 --> 00:02:53.940
but it's a good start.

00:02:53.940 --> 00:02:55.008
A lot of Democrats,

00:02:55.008 --> 00:02:55.542
Dick Durbin,

00:02:55.542 --> 00:02:55.808
the number

00:02:55.808 --> 00:02:56.809
two Democrat in the Senate

00:02:56.809 --> 00:02:58.745
and others have joined on to this.

00:02:58.745 --> 00:02:59.946
The only Republican besides

00:02:59.946 --> 00:03:01.814
tell us who I know is on it is Roy Blunt.

00:03:01.814 --> 00:03:03.349
And he's going to retire in a few days.

00:03:04.717 --> 00:03:05.852
Ron you've

00:03:05.852 --> 00:03:09.022
seen this movie many times over.

00:03:09.088 --> 00:03:11.324
What are your thoughts tonight?

00:03:11.324 --> 00:03:12.625
There's no secret decoder

00:03:12.625 --> 00:03:13.893
ring here, Alisyn.

00:03:13.893 --> 00:03:15.028
I mean, I've been covering this

00:03:15.028 --> 00:03:18.031
since the early 1990 as is Prop one 87.

00:03:18.064 --> 00:03:20.400
And the border is a problem

00:03:20.433 --> 00:03:24.137
that is at best managed not solved.

00:03:24.637 --> 00:03:26.906
But to get a better handle on it.

00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:29.309
The ingredients of a solution

00:03:29.309 --> 00:03:31.444
have been the same for 20 years.

00:03:32.111 --> 00:03:34.714
More money for border enforcement

00:03:34.714 --> 00:03:35.515
and more money

00:03:35.515 --> 00:03:36.683
for the asylum system

00:03:36.683 --> 00:03:38.818
to clean up this huge backlog

00:03:38.818 --> 00:03:40.286
in asylum claims.

00:03:40.286 --> 00:03:41.921
Some path to legal status

00:03:41.921 --> 00:03:44.490
for the people who are here illegally

00:03:44.624 --> 00:03:46.359
And then something that deals

00:03:46.359 --> 00:03:48.294
with the future flow of workers

00:03:48.294 --> 00:03:51.397
after the previous decade 2010 to 2020

00:03:51.798 --> 00:03:53.399
was the smallest population growth

00:03:53.399 --> 00:03:54.300
in American history.

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:56.436
Except for the Depression.

00:03:56.436 --> 00:03:57.737
The Senate passed

00:03:57.737 --> 00:03:59.672
that kind of package in 2006

00:03:59.672 --> 00:04:00.940
on a bipartisan basis

00:04:00.940 --> 00:04:01.908
with Mitch McConnell

00:04:01.908 --> 00:04:03.343
among those voting for it

00:04:03.343 --> 00:04:04.477
under George W Bush.

00:04:04.477 --> 00:04:06.713
The Senate passed that package again

00:04:06.713 --> 00:04:09.249
similar in 2013 on a bipartisan basis

00:04:09.249 --> 00:04:10.650
under Barack Obama

00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:11.517
with Marco

00:04:11.517 --> 00:04:13.086
Rubio among others, voting for it

00:04:13.086 --> 00:04:14.120
each time.

00:04:14.120 --> 00:04:15.121
The Republican controlled

00:04:15.121 --> 00:04:16.856
House would not take it up.

00:04:16.856 --> 00:04:19.592
And if we are going to find a true

00:04:19.993 --> 00:04:22.695
solution that more effectively controls

00:04:22.695 --> 00:04:24.897
the problem, those are the ingredients.

00:04:24.897 --> 00:04:26.132
It's not like a mystery

00:04:26.132 --> 00:04:27.600
or that there's a hidden answer.

00:04:27.600 --> 00:04:28.101
In fact,

00:04:28.101 --> 00:04:29.736
even when Trump was president,

00:04:29.736 --> 00:04:32.305
the Senate Democrats offered him a deal

00:04:32.438 --> 00:04:33.039
to finish

00:04:33.039 --> 00:04:34.140
his border wall

00:04:34.140 --> 00:04:35.942
in return for DOCA legalization,

00:04:35.942 --> 00:04:37.143
and it ran aground.

00:04:37.143 --> 00:04:38.311
When Stephen Miller, another

00:04:38.311 --> 00:04:38.811
in the White House,

00:04:38.811 --> 00:04:41.447
demanded cuts in illegal immigration,

00:04:41.581 --> 00:04:43.182
even amid the slowest population growth

00:04:43.182 --> 00:04:45.551
in any decades except for the Depression.

00:04:45.685 --> 00:04:48.388
So we're going to keep banging

00:04:48.388 --> 00:04:49.789
against each other, red states

00:04:49.789 --> 00:04:51.491
against the federal government, Democrats

00:04:51.491 --> 00:04:52.592
against Republicans,

00:04:53.893 --> 00:04:56.162
indefinitely, until there

00:04:56.162 --> 00:04:57.664
is sort of an awareness

00:04:57.664 --> 00:04:59.198
that the only solution is one

00:04:59.198 --> 00:05:00.033
that is comprehensive

00:05:00.033 --> 00:05:01.200
and you can only get there

00:05:01.200 --> 00:05:02.435
with both parties doing it.

00:05:02.435 --> 00:05:03.670
Neither side can do this

00:05:03.670 --> 00:05:04.771
politically on their own.

00:05:04.771 --> 00:05:07.173
Instead, a new Congress starts next week.

00:05:07.440 --> 00:05:07.740
I mean,

00:05:07.740 --> 00:05:08.775
just because something hasn't

00:05:08.775 --> 00:05:10.176
worked for decades

00:05:10.176 --> 00:05:11.711
doesn't mean that it won't work

00:05:11.711 --> 00:05:12.412
this year.

00:05:12.412 --> 00:05:14.247
Is there any appetite for this?

00:05:14.247 --> 00:05:16.449
I mean, Ron lays out the kind of mountain

00:05:16.683 --> 00:05:17.817
of kind of political will

00:05:17.817 --> 00:05:19.052
that would have to happen

00:05:19.052 --> 00:05:20.720
for this new Congress to take this up.

00:05:20.720 --> 00:05:22.088
And that's because the distance

00:05:22.088 --> 00:05:23.823
between where the Republican base is

00:05:23.823 --> 00:05:25.058
and what the Democratic base on

00:05:25.058 --> 00:05:26.826
this issue are is massive.

00:05:26.826 --> 00:05:28.294
And so politically,

00:05:28.294 --> 00:05:29.662
there is just no real,

00:05:29.662 --> 00:05:31.064
real appetite yet

00:05:31.064 --> 00:05:32.765
to find that sense of common ground.

00:05:32.765 --> 00:05:34.100
And the people, we should say,

00:05:34.100 --> 00:05:35.702
that are hurt most for that

00:05:35.702 --> 00:05:36.669
are the actual migrants

00:05:36.669 --> 00:05:37.370
involved with the

00:05:37.370 --> 00:05:38.304
with the kind of chaotic

00:05:38.304 --> 00:05:40.640
ping pong going back and forth a policy.

00:05:40.640 --> 00:05:41.407
But we can't.

00:05:41.407 --> 00:05:42.909
This is a Republican Congress coming in

00:05:42.909 --> 00:05:43.443
that can't agree

00:05:43.443 --> 00:05:44.677
on the speaker yet

00:05:44.677 --> 00:05:46.245
to to paper over the divisions

00:05:46.245 --> 00:05:47.447
within their caucus.

00:05:47.447 --> 00:05:49.615
There is what's an issue like immigration

00:05:49.716 --> 00:05:51.050
which not only has divisions

00:05:51.050 --> 00:05:52.452
among the Republican caucus,

00:05:52.452 --> 00:05:54.420
but also among the Democratic one.

00:05:54.420 --> 00:05:55.121
It is a

00:05:55.121 --> 00:05:57.056
it is a real tough challenge

00:05:57.056 --> 00:05:58.491
to see the path forward

00:05:58.491 --> 00:05:59.525
for this politically.

00:05:59.525 --> 00:06:01.227
I mean, I think back to the Democratic

00:06:01.227 --> 00:06:02.795
primary years ago

00:06:02.795 --> 00:06:05.031
in 2020 to even nominate Biden.

00:06:05.131 --> 00:06:05.431
And it's

00:06:05.431 --> 00:06:06.466
not as if those candidates

00:06:06.466 --> 00:06:07.233
were laying out

00:06:07.233 --> 00:06:09.268
affirmative immigration policies

00:06:09.268 --> 00:06:10.870
to the folks point in the panel

00:06:10.870 --> 00:06:13.005
they have been running from this issue.

00:06:13.106 --> 00:06:14.340
And so that is

00:06:14.340 --> 00:06:15.842
because there's not a real political

00:06:15.842 --> 00:06:16.576
will there

00:06:16.576 --> 00:06:17.910
to do much of anything about it.

00:06:17.910 --> 00:06:18.277
Scott,

00:06:18.277 --> 00:06:19.078
I want to drill down

00:06:19.078 --> 00:06:19.979
on a couple of things

00:06:19.979 --> 00:06:21.180
that keep coming up

00:06:21.180 --> 00:06:22.682
that people offer as solutions.

00:06:22.682 --> 00:06:24.384
And you mentioned it, which is finishing

00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:26.219
basically a border wall.

00:06:26.219 --> 00:06:27.453
And then Democrats often

00:06:27.453 --> 00:06:29.489
talk about legal status for Dreamers.

00:06:29.756 --> 00:06:31.891
How do either of those solve

00:06:31.891 --> 00:06:36.262
the 1.6 million asylum applications

00:06:36.262 --> 00:06:37.530
that are pending right now

00:06:37.530 --> 00:06:39.265
that are flooding the system?

00:06:39.265 --> 00:06:40.233
It's a seven time

00:06:40.233 --> 00:06:43.202
increase in asylum cases over 2012.

00:06:43.569 --> 00:06:45.204
Three out of ten of them are children.

00:06:45.204 --> 00:06:45.671
How?

00:06:45.705 --> 00:06:47.273
Let's start with yours, the border wall.

00:06:47.273 --> 00:06:48.975
How does how does that stop

00:06:48.975 --> 00:06:50.676
the influx of people

00:06:50.676 --> 00:06:52.812
that are coming from countries

00:06:52.812 --> 00:06:53.780
like Nicaragua?

00:06:53.780 --> 00:06:56.449
Well, with abject poverty and crime,

00:06:57.750 --> 00:06:58.484
well, it

00:06:58.484 --> 00:07:00.386
doesn't fix the backlog in the system.

00:07:00.386 --> 00:07:01.087
What it does do

00:07:01.087 --> 00:07:02.188
if you go ahead and complete

00:07:02.188 --> 00:07:04.223
the barriers like Arizona governor

00:07:04.223 --> 00:07:05.625
outgoing governor Doug Ducey

00:07:05.625 --> 00:07:07.193
tried to do it, just stop people

00:07:07.193 --> 00:07:08.461
from walking across the border.

00:07:08.461 --> 00:07:09.996
I mean, you have people coming in

00:07:09.996 --> 00:07:11.831
to the United States

00:07:11.831 --> 00:07:13.132
across, you know, places

00:07:13.132 --> 00:07:14.500
like the Yuma Gap and Arizona.

00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:15.635
So that's one thing.

00:07:15.635 --> 00:07:17.170
Yeah, but that's the big problem.

00:07:17.170 --> 00:07:20.072
The big problem is the 1.6 million asylum

00:07:20.072 --> 00:07:21.207
applications that that

00:07:21.207 --> 00:07:23.309
our system can't handle.

00:07:23.309 --> 00:07:24.544
I think they're all big problems.

00:07:24.544 --> 00:07:25.411
I think the

00:07:25.411 --> 00:07:26.746
I think the backlog is a problem,

00:07:26.746 --> 00:07:27.346
and I think

00:07:27.346 --> 00:07:29.248
the daily influx is a problem.

00:07:29.248 --> 00:07:30.349
And I do think

00:07:30.349 --> 00:07:31.417
fixing the Dreamers

00:07:31.417 --> 00:07:33.719
situation is also a good thing to do.

00:07:33.753 --> 00:07:35.488
But that also doesn't address

00:07:35.488 --> 00:07:36.889
the people who are showing up

00:07:36.889 --> 00:07:37.857
every single day.

00:07:37.857 --> 00:07:40.560
So there's multi faceted issues here.

00:07:40.827 --> 00:07:41.828
And all of those things,

00:07:41.828 --> 00:07:43.896
I think, wind up in the discussion

00:07:43.896 --> 00:07:44.997
around a possible deal

00:07:44.997 --> 00:07:46.365
because it's what someone wants

00:07:46.365 --> 00:07:46.999
or it's it's

00:07:46.999 --> 00:07:48.601
the most important thing

00:07:48.601 --> 00:07:50.236
for some political constituency.

00:07:50.236 --> 00:07:51.571
So you wind up tacking it on.

00:07:51.571 --> 00:07:52.772
But it strikes me

00:07:52.772 --> 00:07:53.673
that the most important thing

00:07:53.673 --> 00:07:55.074
you could possibly do

00:07:55.074 --> 00:07:57.176
is stop the influx the day.

00:07:57.610 --> 00:07:58.244
Get a handle

00:07:58.244 --> 00:08:00.279
on what we have in terms of the backlog

00:08:00.279 --> 00:08:01.714
and stop adding to it.

00:08:01.714 --> 00:08:02.148
And that,

00:08:02.148 --> 00:08:03.783
I think, is the fundamental disagreement

00:08:03.783 --> 00:08:04.851
between the parties.

